<item>
            <title>[SPR-2533] Support JavaBean Eventing methods in Spring</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2533</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;JavaBeans support the management of listeners via the addX() methods (see section 6 of the JavaBeans specification, titled &quot;Events&quot;). It would be extremely useful to support this in spring so that event listeners could be added to a bean using standard IoC. This could be done either by overloading the meaning of &quot;property&quot; or introducing a new &quot;listener&quot; tag. For instance given the addX() method on a bean you would like to be able to do the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean id=&quot;eventBean&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;property name=&quot;X&quot; ref=&quot;listener1&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;property name=&quot;X&quot; ref=&quot;listener2&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean id=&quot;listener1/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;bean id=&quot;listener2/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="14908">SPR-2533</key>
            <summary>Support JavaBean Eventing methods in Spring</summary>
