                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="20651" author="stolsvik" created="Sat, 4 Nov 2006 22:55:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2801&quot; title=&quot;&amp;quot;adder&amp;quot; injection in addition to &amp;quot;setter&amp;quot; (invoke addXX() instead of setXX())&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-2801&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-2801&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which asks for a more generic version of the same (&quot;adder&quot; injection compared to &quot;setter&quot; injection).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20696" author="jcsahnwaldt" created="Thu, 9 Nov 2006 01:30:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Maybe this should be made explicit? Something like this?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;bean id=&quot;eventBean&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;property name=&quot;X&quot; ref=&quot;listener1&quot; action=&quot;add&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;property name=&quot;X&quot; ref=&quot;listener2&quot; action=&quot;add&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="20706" author="jcsahnwaldt" created="Thu, 9 Nov 2006 05:00:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The oldest and most active issue regarding this feature seems to be &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-230&quot; title=&quot;Please improve BeanFactory support for containers &amp;amp; collections&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-230&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-230&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="68192" author="cbeams" created="Thu, 7 Jul 2011 18:15:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please take a look at the resolution comments for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-230&quot; title=&quot;Please improve BeanFactory support for containers &amp;amp; collections&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SPR-230&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SPR-230&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which explain how in Spring 3.0/3.1 the code-based &lt;tt&gt;@Configuration&lt;/tt&gt; class approach can meet the needs described here.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
